# Rik's Cantina - Behind the scenes[]

In the current Star Wars canon, Rik's Cantina was mentioned in "Coruscant Underworld," an article written by Mark Newbold and published in the "Guide to the Galaxy" department of the twenty-sixth issue of De Agostini's Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon magazine, which released around July 1, 2015.

The cantina originated in the Star Wars Legends continuity, where it was first mentioned as just "Rik's" in Star Wars: Legacy 0, a pre-release supplement for the Star Wars: Legacy comic book series written by John Ostrander and published by Dark Horse Comics on June 7, 2006. It then appeared for the first time in the fourteenth issue of Star Wars: Legacy, and was first identified as Rik's Cantina in the sixteenth issue, with both issues written by Ostrander and Jan Duursema, illustrated by Duursema, and published on July 11, and September 12, 2007, respectively.
metadata.title: Rik's Cantina

metadata.content:
# Mos Espa's first cantina - Behind the scenes[]

In the current Star Wars canon, Mos Espa's first cantina was mentioned in the 2016 reference book Star Wars: Complete Locations. It was part of material reprinted from the 2000 reference book Inside the Worlds of Star Wars: Episode I, which was written by Kristin Lund and marked the first mention of the cantina in the Star Wars Legends continuity.
metadata.title: Mos Espa's first cantina

"Your Love Sends me to Level 9"


Publication information

Release date
By 382 BBY


Type
Song

"Your Love Sends Me to Level 9" was a popular song in 382 BBY, when the band at the Raik's Parlor gambling den on the planet Coruscant began playing the song. The human Axel Greylark, a patron there, found it irritatingly popular.

# Roldalna - Behind the scenes[]

Roldalna first appeared in "The Package," a Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game adventure written by Dave Marron and published by West End Games in the 1993 book Twin Stars of Kira.

The 2009 reference book The Essential Atlas placed the Roldalna system, and therefore Roldalna itself, in grid square N-15 as part of the Expansion Region. The book also depicted the system on a map, albeit in the Mid Rim, grid square N-16. The StarWars.com Online Companion to The Essential Atlas later provided a placement of Expansion Region, grid square N-16, which this article assumes to be correct.
metadata.title: Roldalna

The novel was published on November 22, 2022. Prior to its release, the mention of the gems was included in a StarWars.com preview for the novel on October 4 of that year.
